The paper is about constructing a large-scale benchmark for face forgery detection, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques. The dataset is generated using a newly proposed end-to-end face swapping framework, which involves machine learning (MM) techniques. The paper also discusses the evaluation of different detection baselines, which involves machine learning and data analysis (LG) techniques. The topic of face forgery detection also falls under the category of cybersecurity (CR), which is another likely sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for generating fake videos and evaluating detection baselines suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (AI).
